  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Administrator User Management provides comprehensive control over user accounts on the platform. This includes viewing user details, editing account information, managing passwords, controlling account status, and maintaining security through proper user lifecycle management.</p>

  <h3>Access Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Administrator Privileges</strong> — Must be logged in with admin role</li>
    <li><strong>Secure Environment</strong> — All user management actions are audited</li>
    <li><strong>Data Protection</strong> — Handle user data according to privacy regulations</li>
    <li><strong>Direct Access</strong> — Available via `/admin/users`</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>User Management Capabilities</h3>

  <h4>Account Administration</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>View All Users</strong> — Complete list of registered users with search and filtering</li>
    <li><strong>Edit User Details</strong> — Modify user information including contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Password Management</strong> — Reset user passwords securely</li>
    <li><strong>Account Status Control</strong> — Activate, deactivate, or suspend user accounts</li>
    <li><strong>Account Deletion</strong> — Remove user accounts with proper validation</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Security & Compliance</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Audit Logging</strong> — All user management actions are logged</li>
    <li><strong>Access Control</strong> — Role-based permissions for user operations</li>
    <li><strong>Data Privacy</strong> — Secure handling of personal user information</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance Tracking</strong> — Maintain records for regulatory compliance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Accessing User Management</h3>

  <h4>From Admin Dashboard</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Open Admin Dashboard</strong> — Navigate to `/admin/dashboard`</li>
    <li><strong>Click Users Card</strong> — Click on the "Total Users" statistics card</li>
    <li><strong>Access User Management</strong> — Click "Manage Users" link in the card footer</li>
    <li><strong>View User List</strong> — See all users with management options</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Direct Navigation</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Direct URL</strong> — Go directly to `/admin/users`</li>
    <li><strong>Admin Menu</strong> — Access through administrator navigation menu</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Actions</strong> — Shortcuts from other admin pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Viewing and Searching Users</h3>

  <h4>User List Interface</h4>

  <h5>User Table Columns</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Name</strong> — User's full name (first and last)</li>
    <li><strong>Email</strong> — Primary email address for account</li>
    <li><strong>Club</strong> — Associated club (if applicable)</li>
    <li><strong>Role</strong> — User role (Standard User, Club Delegate, Administrator)</li>
    <li><strong>Status</strong> — Account status (Active, Inactive)</li>
    <li><strong>Registration Date</strong> — When the user account was created</li>
    <li><strong>Last Login</strong> — Most recent login activity</li>
    <li><strong>Actions</strong> — Available management actions for each user</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Table Features</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sorting</strong> — Click column headers to sort by that field</li>
    <li><strong>Pagination</strong> — Navigate through large user lists</li>
    <li><strong>Page Size</strong> — Control number of users displayed per page</li>
    <li><strong>Export Options</strong> — Export user data for external analysis</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Search and Filtering</h4>

  <h5>Search Functionality</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Name Search</strong> — Search by first name, last name, or both</li>
    <li><strong>Email Search</strong> — Find users by email address</li>
    <li><strong>Club Search</strong> — Filter users by associated club</li>
    <li><strong>Global Search</strong> — Search across multiple fields simultaneously</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Advanced Filtering</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Status Filter</strong> — Show only active or inactive users</li>
    <li><strong>Role Filter</strong> — Filter by user role or permission level</li>
    <li><strong>Date Range</strong> — Filter by registration date or last login</li>
    <li><strong>Club Association</strong> — Show users with or without club associations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Editing User Accounts</h3>

  <h4>Accessing User Edit</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Select User</strong> — Find the user in the user management list</li>
    <li><strong>Click Edit</strong> — Click the "Edit" button in the Actions column</li>
    <li><strong>Open Edit Form</strong> — User edit form will open with current details</li>
    <li><strong>Modify Information</strong> — Update user details as needed</li>
    <li><strong>Save Changes</strong> — Apply the modifications to the user account</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Editable User Fields</h4>

  <h5>Personal Information</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>First Name</strong> — User's given name (2-50 characters)</li>
    <li><strong>Last Name</strong> — User's family name (2-50 characters)</li>
    <li><strong>Email Address</strong> — Primary contact email (must be valid format)</li>
    <li><strong>Phone Number</strong> — Contact phone number (optional, max 20 characters)</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Account Settings</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Club Association</strong> — Link user to a specific club</li>
    <li><strong>Role Assignment</strong> — Set user role and permissions</li>
    <li><strong>Account Status</strong> — Control active/inactive status</li>
    <li><strong>Profile Visibility</strong> — Control public profile visibility</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Form Validation</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Required Fields</strong> — First name, last name, and email are mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>Email Format</strong> — Email must be in valid format</li>
    <li><strong>Name Length</strong> — Names must be between 2-50 characters</li>
    <li><strong>Phone Format</strong> — Phone numbers limited to 20 characters</li>
    <li><strong>Unique Email</strong> — Email addresses must be unique across all users</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Password Management</h3>

  <h4>Password Reset Process</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Select User</strong> — Choose the user requiring password reset</li>
    <li><strong>Click Reset Password</strong> — Click "Reset Password" in the Actions column</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Action</strong> — Confirm the password reset request</li>
    <li><strong>System Generates Reset</strong> — Platform creates secure reset token</li>
    <li><strong>User Receives Email</strong> — User gets password reset instructions</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Security Considerations</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Secure Tokens</strong> — Reset tokens are cryptographically secure</li>
    <li><strong>Expiration Time</strong> — Reset links expire after a set time period</li>
    <li><strong>Single Use</strong> — Each reset token can only be used once</li>
    <li><strong>Audit Logging</strong> — All password reset actions are logged</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Manual Password Setting</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency Access</strong> — For urgent account access needs</li>
    <li><strong>Temporary Passwords</strong> — Set temporary passwords that expire</li>
    <li><strong>Security Notification</strong> — Notify users of manual password changes</li>
    <li><strong>Password Policy</strong> — Ensure passwords meet security requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Account Status Management</h3>

  <h4>Activating/Deactivating Accounts</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Select User</strong> — Choose the user account to modify</li>
    <li><strong>Click Status Toggle</strong> — Click "Toggle Status" in the Actions column</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Action</strong> — Confirm the status change</li>
    <li><strong>Status Updates</strong> — Account status changes immediately</li>
    <li><strong>User Notification</strong> — Consider notifying user of status change</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Status Implications</h4>

  <h5>Active Status</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Full Access</strong> — User can log in and access all authorized features</li>
    <li><strong>Club Participation</strong> — Can participate in club activities and events</li>
    <li><strong>Email Communications</strong> — Receives platform emails and notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Profile Visibility</strong> — Profile visible to other users as configured</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Inactive Status</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Login Blocked</strong> — User cannot log into the platform</li>
    <li><strong>Limited Access</strong> — No access to account features or data</li>
    <li><strong>Email Suspension</strong> — Stops receiving platform communications</li>
    <li><strong>Data Preservation</strong> — Account data remains but is inaccessible</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deleting User Accounts</h3>

  <h4>Account Deletion Process</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Select User</strong> — Choose the user account for deletion</li>
    <li><strong>Click Delete</strong> — Click "Delete" in the Actions column</li>
    <li><strong>Review Dependencies</strong> — System checks for related data and dependencies</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Deletion</strong> — Confirm the permanent deletion</li>
    <li><strong>Data Removal</strong> — Account and associated data are permanently removed</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Deletion Considerations</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Data Dependencies</strong> — Check for carnival registrations, team memberships, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Club Associations</strong> — Consider impact on club management</li>
    <li><strong>Historical Data</strong> — Audit logs and historical records may reference the user</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory Compliance</strong> — Ensure deletion complies with data retention policies</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Data Handling Options</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Complete Removal</strong> — Delete all user data permanently</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymize Data</strong> — Replace personal data with anonymous identifiers</li>
    <li><strong>Archive Data</strong> — Move data to archive for compliance purposes</li>
    <li><strong>Soft Delete</strong> — Mark as deleted but preserve data structure</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>User Management Best Practices</h3>

  <h4>Security & Privacy</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access Control</strong> — Limit admin access to authorized personnel only</li>
    <li><strong>Audit Everything</strong> — Log all user management actions for security</li>
    <li><strong>Data Protection</strong> — Handle personal information according to privacy laws</li>
    <li><strong>Secure Communication</strong> — Use secure channels for password resets</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Operational Efficiency</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bulk Operations</strong> — Use bulk tools for multiple user updates</li>
    <li><strong>Search Optimization</strong> — Use filters to quickly find specific users</li>
    <li><strong>Regular Maintenance</strong> — Periodically review and clean up inactive accounts</li>
    <li><strong>Documentation</strong> — Keep records of user management decisions</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>User Experience</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Clear Communication</strong> — Inform users of account changes</li>
    <li><strong>Support Access</strong> — Provide clear support channels for user issues</li>
    <li><strong>Password Security</strong> — Educate users on password best practices</li>
    <li><strong>Account Recovery</strong> — Ensure users can recover access when needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Troubleshooting User Issues</h3>

  <h4>Common User Problems</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Login Failures</strong> — Check account status and password validity</li>
    <li><strong>Email Issues</strong> — Verify email address and delivery settings</li>
    <li><strong>Permission Problems</strong> — Review user roles and club associations</li>
    <li><strong>Data Inconsistencies</strong> — Check for data integrity issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Resolution Strategies</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Status Verification</strong> — Ensure account is active and properly configured</li>
    <li><strong>Password Reset</strong> — Use secure password reset for access issues</li>
    <li><strong>Role Adjustment</strong> — Modify user roles to fix permission problems</li>
    <li><strong>Data Correction</strong> — Fix any data inconsistencies in user records</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Integration with Other Systems</h3>

  <h4>Club Management Integration</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Club Association</strong> — Link users to clubs for proper access control</li>
    <li><strong>Delegate Roles</strong> — Manage club delegate permissions and responsibilities</li>
    <li><strong>Club Data</strong> — Access club information when managing users</li>
    <li><strong>Club Communication</strong> — Coordinate with club administrators</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Carnival Integration</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Registration Tracking</strong> — Monitor user carnival registrations</li>
    <li><strong>Team Membership</strong> — Track user participation in carnival teams</li>
    <li><strong>Event Access</strong> — Control user access to carnival management</li>
    <li><strong>Communication</strong> — Manage carnival-related user communications</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Audit Integration</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Activity Logging</strong> — All user management actions are audited</li>
    <li><strong>Security Monitoring</strong> — Track suspicious user management activity</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance Reporting</strong> — Generate reports for regulatory compliance</li>
    <li><strong>Historical Tracking</strong> — Maintain complete user lifecycle history</li>
  </ul>

